cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with evaluating grammatical error corrections. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields are closely related to natural language processing. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are often used in natural language processing tasks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with improving the accuracy of language processing tools, which has implications for society.
